[log] bash[68] stdout ##### Key Attributes
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_options`: Stores command-line option configurations
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_command_decorator_info`: Stores information for all `@command` decorators
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_subtype_init_info`: Stores information for all `@subtype` decorators
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_enum_mapping`: Stores mapping relationships for enum types
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_commands`: Stores all registered commands
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_command_aliases`: Stores command aliases
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_parsers`: Stores argument parsers
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_subparsers`: Stores subcommand parsers
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_enum_flag_default_cleared`: Tracks which flag parameters have had their default values cleared
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_is_calling_target`: Indicates whether the target command is currently being called
[log] bash[68] stdout - `_current_parser`: The argument parser for the current command
[log] bash[68] stdout ##### Key Methods
[log] bash[68] stdout - `__init__()`: Initializes the context, setting all attributes to their initial state
[log] bash[68] stdout - `reset()`: Resets the context state, clearing all stored information
[log] bash[68] stdout - `get_version_flags()`: Retrieves version flag configuration
[log] bash[68] stdout   - Returns: A tuple of version flags, e.g., `("--version",)` or `("-v", "--version")`
[log] bash[68] stdout ## Usage Example
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout # Get singleton instance
[log] bash[68] stdout ctx = _Context()
[log] bash[68] stdout # Reset state
[log] bash[68] stdout ctx.reset()
[log] bash[68] stdout # Set options
[log] bash[68] stdout class Options:
[log] bash[68] stdout     def __init__(self):
[log] bash[68] stdout         self.version_flag = ("-v", "--version")
[log] bash[68] stdout ctx._options = Options()
[log] bash[68] stdout # Get version flags
[log] bash[68] stdout print(ctx.get_version_flags())  # Output: ('-v', '--version')
[log] bash[68] stdout ```
[log] bash[68] stdout ### Actual Usage Modes
[log] bash[68] stdout #### Basic Usage
[log] bash[68] stdout ```python
[log] bash[68] stdout import arguably
[log] bash[68] stdout @arguably.command
[log] bash[68] stdout def hello(name: str, age: int = 30, verbose: bool = False):
[log] bash[68] stdout     """
[log] bash[68] stdout     Greet the user
[log] bash[68] stdout     
[log] bash[68] stdout     Args:
[log] bash[68] stdout         name: The user's name
[log] bash[68] stdout         age: The user's age
[log] bash[68] stdout         verbose: Whether to display detailed information
[log] bash[68] stdout     """
[log] bash[68] stdout     if verbose:
[log] bash[68] stdout         print(f"Detailed greeting: Hello, {name}! You are {age} years old.")
[log] bash[68] stdout     else:
[log] bash[68] stdout         print(f"Hello, {name}!")
[log] bash[68] stdout if __name__ == "__main__":
